"Spring Awakening" is another period musical set in late 19th century Germany that uses an alternative rock style to convey the message of coming of age and teen angst. I think the song really conveys the idea of standing out and being different which fits the setting of a circus.

I am sorry, but it is pure exploitation.Iâ€™m sick of the recent trend in movies to use the subject of someone living life with a disability as â€˜inspirational.â€™ My disability shouldnâ€™t be used as an inspirational story. I live a productive and fulfilling life because there is no reason I shouldnâ€™t. Period. That shouldnâ€™t be treated as surprising or extraordinary.It may have been different if the movieâ€™s central character was one of the actual disabled performers in Barnumâ€™s circus. Or if the movie was about the real life of a disability advocate from that era. Hell, even a made up able-bodied white male circus owner would have been better than this. But it is impossible to separate the fictional character from the real life PT Barnum and his dark exploitative show. Not when it is so recent.
